---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { generateOrganizationSchema } from "../lib/schema";

const schema = generateOrganizationSchema();
---

<Layout
  title="About - White Rabbit WCS"
  description="The story of Arizona's premier West Coast Swing community. Follow the white rabbit into a world where community comes first."
  type="website"
  schema={schema}
>
  <main class="about-page">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="page-header">
        <h1 class="page-title gradient-text">Follow the White Rabbit</h1>
        <p class="page-subtitle">
          Arizona's Premier WCS Community
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="story-content">
        <section class="story-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">> The Beginning</h2>
          <p>
            In 2018-2019, Phoenix's West Coast Swing scene had stalled. Younger
            dancers craved modern music and fresh energy, but established venues
            weren't listening. With the advent of the COVID lockdown, our community nearly ceased to exist. When restrictions lifted in Arizona, we saw
            an opportunity.
          </p>
          <p>
            What started as intimate speakeasy-style home socials, just friends
            dancing in living rooms, evolved into something extraordinary.
            During our final home event, a joke about "90's rave style"
            marketing with bunny stencils and a "Follow the White Rabbit" 
            message (ala "The Matrix") sparked something real. The name stuck, and the White Rabbit
            Society was born.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="story-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">> Community First, Always 💚</h2>
          <p>
            White Rabbit is about people and community, about connecting through a medium we all love. We operate on a
            simple philosophy: create the best social dance experience we can, and everything
            else follows. To that end, the White Rabbit Society Code of Conduct:
- If it glows it won't say no.
- This is a safe space, all are welcome. Be good to each other.
- No unsolicited feedback on the dance floor.
          </p>
          <p>
            We encourage feedback from you, our fellow bunnies. Real voices. Real input. Real
            effort. This isn't just a community, it's a way of life, and we're all in it together. From 24 dancers
            in a tiny venue to 200 at our monthly socials, we've grown because
            we care, and because you do too.
          </p>
          <p>
            We celebrate what matters: connection, growth, and the joy of music and dance.
            Our annual Social Dance Champions aren't crowned by judges. They're
            chosen by you, the community, through democratic voting.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="story-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">> What Makes Us Different</h2>
          <p>
            We believe in going far, together. Not fast, alone. This philosophy
            shapes everything we do:
          </p>
          <ul class="features-list">
            <li>
              <strong>Modern Energy:</strong> Contemporary music, fresh vibes, and
              an atmosphere that welcomes everyone
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>True Community:</strong> Real-time feedback here on the site, democratic voting,
              and genuine care for every dancer's experience. Contact us at <a href="mailto:whiterabbitwcs@gmail.com">whiterabbitwcs@gmail.com</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>All Levels Welcome:</strong> Whether you're stepping onto the
              floor for the first time or you're a seasoned pro, and no matter your dance background, you have a home at White Rabbit
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Phoenix Proud:</strong> We're building something special right
              here in the Sonoran Desert, and we want you to be part of it
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="story-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">> The Journey Continues</h2>
          <p>
            From speakeasy socials to Arizona's biggest monthly West Coast Swing
            event, White Rabbit is a
            movement. A place where the music is modern, the energy is electric,
            and every dancer matters.
          </p>
<p>
The White Rabbit Society is led by "The Tripod," our three Event Directors: <a href=https://www.instagram.com/herrington.ftw/ target="blank>Joe Herrington</a> (Music/Creative Director), 
<a href=https://www.instagram.com/sgem612/ target="blank">Sarah Hightower</a> (Administrative/Financial Director), and <a href=https://www.instagram.com/ninja.dance.az/ target="blank">Travis Swartzlander</a> (Talent/Education/Promotions Director). 
Feel free to hit up our socials on IG and Facebook. Email us at: <a href="mailto:whiterabbitwcs@gmail.com">whiterabbitwcs@gmail.com</a>
          <p>
            The white rabbit led us down this path. His name is <a href=https://tinyurl.com/24e7nc76 target="blank">Nivens McTwisp</a>, and we follow him still. We invite you to
            follow him too.
          </p>
          <p class="cta-text">Ready to see how deep the rabbit hole goes?</p>
        </section>

        <div class="quote-block">
          <blockquote>
            "You're here because you know something. What you know you can't explain, but you feel it.<br />
            You've felt it your entire life...I can only show you the door, you must walk (walk, triple-step) through it."
          </blockquote>
          <cite>— Morpheus</cite>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    padding: 3rem 0;
    min-height: calc(100vh - 80px);
  }

  .page-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 8vw, 4rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  }

  .page-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .story-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .story-section {
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .section-icon {
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-primary);
  }

  .story-section p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .features-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .features-list li {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-left: 2rem;
    position: relative;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .features-list li::before {
    content: "▸";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }

  .features-list strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .quote-block {
    margin: 4rem 0;
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-primary);
    text-align: center;
  }

  blockquote {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  cite {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-style: normal;
  }

  .cta-text {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-page {
      padding: 2rem 0;
    }

    .page-header {
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .story-section {
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .section-icon {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .section-title {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .story-section p,
    .features-list li {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    blockquote {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
    }

    .quote-block {
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
